w:r.w:t: Procedure to Manually Backup Production Data
Login to the AWS console at
Select the Volumes item in the left menu
Click on the check box for the production volume
Click on Create Snapshot in the top right
Enter a description in the pop-up. Use the convention “Production mm-dd-yyyy”
You can view the snapshots by selecting Snapshots from the left side menu.
Repeat the above procedure for the Test13 volume at least once a week.
From the snapshots screen you can delete any old snap shots you don't need.
Develop a snapshot retention plan based on site volume. For Test13 you can backup once a week and keep one per month.

consider daily snapshots where you keep all snapshots for at least a week. Every Sunday delete the Monday-Saturday snapshots from two weeks prior. This way you will have 7 backups on hand for the last week.
